## M20i.1: resource Vec iteration without `?` source borrow is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5's M20i.1 design pass: bare-source iteration over
## `Vec(*Closure())` (or any resource-element Vec) would silently
## yield a strong handle copy per iteration without bumping the
## refcount. Sema requires the explicit `?vec` source borrow so
## the ownership layer can install the loop-borrow on `subs` AND
## bind the element as a borrowed view of the slot. The
## diagnostic points at the fix.

sub main()
  count: *Cell(Int) = *Cell(value: 0)
  cb1: *Closure() = *Closure(|+count| count.set(count.get() + 1))

  subs: Vec(*Closure()) = Vec()
  (!subs).push(+cb1)

  for cb in subs
    cb()
